Party's long history of political dominance has both advantages and
disadvantages in Mexico's election, former President Jimmy Carter
said in a one-on-one interview as he
</P>
<P>
   visited polling places Sunday. Carter acknowledged that PRI
officials were using the government's powers to pressure voters,
but said the party's long record also left it vulnerable to the
people's dissatisfactions. (Ferriss, Cox News Service).
