   LONDON-AUCTIONS (London) _ As collectors and dealers gathered
here last week for Christie's and Sotheby's big sales of
Impressionist, modern, and contemporary art, the auction houses'
legal troubles in the United States seemed to make no difference to
the buyers. By Carol Vogel.
</P>
