</P>
<P>
   (Coding varies.)
</P>
<P>
   CNN-MEDIA (Atlanta) _ A real-estate expansion by Turner
Broadcasting in Atlanta could indicate an expanded role for CNN.com
if the AOL-Time Warner merger goes through. By Jonathan Robinson.
</P>
<P>
   TV-LOCALNEWS-MEDIA (Chicago) _ A Chicago news station, WBBM-TV,
shifts to a serious news format, throwing out the local news
playbook of pizazz and sensationalism in use at television stations
throughout the country for two decades. In Chicago _ the home of
Siskel and Ebert and a town with a rich history of brawling,
innovative television news _ the experiment is ripe in irony: If
there is a gimmick in all of this, it is that there is no gimmick.
The gambit is being watched in cities and towns across the nation
by station managers who have been unable to stem the loss of
viewers of their local news programs, from which they derive much
of their advertising revenues. Though all broadcast TV programs
have been losing audience amid increased competition from cable and
the Internet during recent years, none seem to be doing so at the
same rate as local news. By Jim Rutenberg.
</P>
