   TV-LOCALNEWS-MEDIA (Chicago) _ A Chicago news station, WBBM-TV,
shifts to a serious news format, throwing out the local news
playbook of pizazz and sensationalism in use at television stations
throughout the country for two decades. In Chicago _ a town with a
rich history of brawling, innovative television news _ the
experiment is ripe in irony: If there is a gimmick in all of this,
it is that there is no gimmick. The gambit is being watched in
cities and towns across the nation by station managers who have
been unable to stem the loss of viewers of their local news
programs, from which they derive much of their advertising
revenues. By Jim Rutenberg.
