<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs on
Monday, July 3, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact William Toren at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   HACKER-HERO (Thousand Oaks, Calif.) _ Five years ago, Kevin
Mitnick was a desperate criminal on the run from the FBI as the
most-wanted computer hacker in the country, and a hero to the
underground hacker community. Today, he's served his time but
remains a figure of admiration, in demand not only by his hacker
fans, but also by the same government agencies he penetrated and
burglarized. By Troy Anderson. (Will move in the ``a'' national and
``n'' California state news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DNC-PROTESTERS (Los Angeles) _ With 50,000 protesters expected
to fill the streets of Los Angeles for the Democratic National
Convention, organizers are having to coordinate a wide variety of
agendas and activities. While no one is advocating violence, many
concede it has its uses as a tool for publicity. By Beth Barrett.
(Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California state news
file.)
</P>
