hills of Jerusalem, a deeply rooted phenomenon in the culture of
the Jewish diaspora. Though no agronomist, Stabler could look
around him and tell that the hillside area in Jerusalem was not the
most fertile ground. So it came as no shock to him to learn that
most of the saplings planted by his family would not survive. (Rina
Castelnuovo/The New York Times)
</P>
